# StoneRise SaaS-Style Graphics (Organic LinkedIn)

Use this when remaking StoneRise product screenshots into clean, modern visuals for founder/employee LinkedIn posts (not paid ads).

## Must-Haves

- **Look like product design, not an advert**: no big headlines, no CTA buttons, no "Book a demo", no promotional badges
- **Keep the UI truthful**: preserve the same feature/flow shown; don't invent UI elements or claims
- **Use the official logo**: `Marketing/Brand/stonerise-logo.png` (small, subtle; plenty of padding)

---

## Two Graphic Styles

Choose the appropriate style based on content and context.

### Style A — Polished Screenshot (Browser Frame)

Best for: showing a specific workflow, form, or single-screen feature in context.

- Place UI inside a clean browser/app window frame (rounded corners, thin top bar with traffic-light dots)
- Soft gradient background behind the frame
- Subtle drop shadow on the frame
- Logo placed small outside the frame (bottom-right corner)

### Style B — Conceptual Floating UI (Layered Cards)

Best for: dashboards, analytics, multi-element features, or conveying capability without showing exact screens.

**Composition:**
- Multiple UI cards/panels floating and overlapping at slight angles
- No browser frame — elements float freely on the background
- Layered depth with soft shadows between cards
- Call-out stat badges or progress rings to highlight key metrics

**Visual language:**
- Stylised, simplified data (clean tables, rounded charts, branded accent colours)
- Soft, light gradient background (off-white to pale blue/green/grey)
- Generous whitespace; avoid clutter
- Accent colours from StoneRise palette (greens, blues) for highlights, icons, progress bars

**Examples of card types:**
- Data tables (severity, status, amounts)
- Line/area charts showing trends over time
- Stat call-outs ("52 Identified", "Approval delays reduced by 75%")
- Progress rings or status indicators
- Workflow node snippets

---

## Shared Guidelines (Both Styles)

### Palette
- **Backgrounds:** light neutrals — off-white, pale grey, soft gradients
- **Accents:** StoneRise green (#00A86B) and blue (#1E5AA8) for highlights, icons, progress elements
- **Text:** dark navy/charcoal for readability

### Legibility
- All text must be readable at LinkedIn mobile feed size (~1080×1080 displayed at ~500px)
- Minimum effective font size ~14px at final resolution

### Branding
- Include StoneRise logo subtly (small, bottom-right or bottom-centre, outside main UI elements)
- Do not over-brand; this is organic content, not an ad

## Avoid

- Heavy noise, harsh glows, gimmicky 3D, or overly "salesy" layouts
- Over-branding: keep logo and accents understated
- Inventing UI elements or stats not present in the source material
- Browser chrome for Style B (floating UI should not have window frames)
